album.author: Skatenigs
album.description:
AUSTIN, TX. - Skatenigs, the long-running electro-thrashcore outfit led by singer Phil "Phildo" Owen, return to the musical stage with What Could Go Wrong?, a collection of all-new recordings, on Armalyte Industries on October 29.
Featuring the current core Skatenigs crew of Owen, Chris Ahrens and Adam Lamar on guitars, and live drummer/studio bassist Myke Bingham (Owen: "He's a one-man rhythm section!"), the 12-track physical CD release will be followed by its digital streaming counterpart via Cleopatra Records on Halloween.
Skatenigs was begun by Owen in Los Angeles in 1989, though it's been Austin-based since the early '90s. Running until 1995...

                                                              -Dr. Ron Paul

My name is Ariel. I love my family, and I detest tyranny, and crimes against humanity.
My original inspiration for this album came by learning about my nation’s horrific foreign policies, which result in untold millions of innocent deaths.

album.author: Sir TJ The Wrathful
album.description:
In 2008, I locked myself in A room with a banjo and this is what came out. This is NOT typical, out of tune, twangy banjo music. I would say this is relaxing, acoustic, instrumental music. I made this as a solo project while performing with The Doerfels, the band I started with four of my younger brothers and our only sister. 
Anyways, If you dare to listen, Beware of Banjo!
If you receive any value from this music, which I loved making, please let me know with any kind of value! ITM TYFYC KTLD,
Sir TJ The Wrathful

I made this as a solo project while performing with The Doerfels, the band I started with four of my younger brothers and our only sister. 
Anyways, If you dare to listen, Beware of Banjo!
If you receive any value from this music, which I loved making, please let me know with any kind of value! ITM TYFYC KTLD,
Sir TJ The Wrathful

album.author: False Finish
album.description: As you press play on "Home Sweet Home (The Dream of Love Survives but it Disappoints Constantly)," the opening notes of the electronic instrumental album send a shiver down your spine. The haunting melodies and dissonant harmonies seem to echo through the empty spaces of a world long forgotten, evoking images of a desolate landscape where hope and happiness are distant memories. The album's electronic instrumentation is both eerie and ethereal, capturing the shattered and broken nature of a dystopian world in a hauntingly beautiful way. The persistent dream of love that survives, but disappoints constantly, is a poignant reminder...
album.title: Home Sweet Home (The Dream of Love Survives but it Disappoints Constantly)

The album's electronic instrumentation is both eerie and ethereal, capturing the shattered and broken nature of a dystopian world in a hauntingly beautiful way. The persistent dream of love that survives, but disappoints constantly, is a poignant reminder...
album.title: Home Sweet Home (The Dream of Love Survives but it Disappoints Constantly)

album.author: The Lightningrod Salesman
album.description:
Dive into this lush world of musical experimentation, where real instruments mix with electronic ones, where beauty and fear struggle for dominance, where nature and song breathe warm life into the cold climate of synthetic sounds.
The concept for this album starts with the idea of a tribe in the isolated jungle, hidden away from civilization, practicing the old, beautiful ways of survival.
From there it may take you many places.
Enjoy

copyright Ariel Powell 2005

album.description: by Robert Willey (1993).Hardware:Macintosh SE computerRoland Sound Canvas moduleYamaha KX76 keyboard controllerKorg Wavestation synthesizerMackie 1602 mixerLexicon LXP-1 reverbPanasonic SV-3700 DAT recorderSoftware:Studio Vision (Opcode)Intelligent Music UpBeat (David Zicarelli)Programmable Instruments (Robert Willey)The sounds and processes had a big effect on the musical ideas, textures, and forms. UpBeat was a cool program that was used on half the album's songs. It allowed the user to set boundaries on random events that varied the notes you played, creating variations in drum pitch patterns. I think the fun of working in this environment comes through in the recordings. The era ended...

title: We're in It for the Money

album.author: Choreboy
album.description: Punk rock may be a traditionally tricky intersection for art and commerce, but former Skatenig Phil Owen has chosen his side. "Everything is for sale," says Owen. In fact, one could say this statement of purpose is at the heart of Choreboy, Owen's retro-punk side-project he founded alongside former Big Boy Chris Gates and fellow Skatenig alumnus Mat Mitchell. Fittingly, then, "We're in It for the Money" is Choreboy's anthem, as well as the lead-off track from the group's debut, Good Clean Fun… My Ass, a punchy little album from a project Owen says takes its name from a scrubbing pa...
